'''Miwa Shrine''' (みわじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Aza Kitanakajō, {{ill|lt=Tsubata|Q432014|qid=Q432014|1=Tsubata, Ishikawa}}, {{ill|lt=Kahoku District|Q1130942|qid=Q1130942|1=Kahoku District, Ishikawa}}, {{ill|lt=Ishikawa Prefecture|Q131281|qid=Q131281|1=Ishikawa Prefecture}}. It stands in the hills behind {{ill|lt=Tsubata Station|Q3701490|qid=Q3701490|1=Tsubata Station}}. Its {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=former shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qid=Q712534}} was {{ill|lt=Sonsha|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
It enshrines eight deities: {{ill|qid=Q10936701|lt=Ōmononushi|Q867534|qid=Q867534|qid=Q10936701|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōmononushi}}, {{ill|lt=Kikurihime|Q11619891|qid=Q11619891|lt=Kikurihime-no-Kami|1=Kikurihime}}, {{ill|qid=Q1107286|lt=Futsunushi|Q21391580|qid=Q21391580|qid=Q1107286|lt=Futsunushi-no-Mikoto|1=Futsunushi}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q1502690|lt=Takemikazuchi-no-Kami|1=Takemikazuchi}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane|qid=Q2564508}}, {{ill|lt=Himegami|Q22070227|qid=Q22070227|1=Himegami}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|1=Ukanomitama}}, and {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q10935105|lt=Ōyamakui-no-Mikoto|1=Oyamakui no Kami}}.

=== Origin ===
Its founding is said to be {{ill|lt=836|Q24957|qid=Q24957|1=836}} ({{ill|lt=Jōwa (Japan)|Q1075605|qid=Q1075605|lt=Jōwa|1=Jōwa (Heian period)}} 3), and it is considered the minor shrine "Miwa Shrine" in Kaga District, {{ill|lt=Kaga Province|Q864166|qid=Q864166|1=Ise Province}}, in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}<ref>Another candidate {{ill|lt=ronsha|Q135022904|qid=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}} is {{ill|lt=Ishiura Shrine|Q11586806|qid=Q11586806|1=Ishiura Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kanazawa|Q191130|qid=Q191130|1=Kanazawa}}.</ref>. There is a pond in the precincts called Ryūjin-no-Ike.

=== Access ===
* 10 minutes on foot from Tsubata Station on {{ill|lt=West Japan Railway Company|Q502125|qid=Q502125|1=West Japan Railway Company}} (JR West) and {{ill|lt=IR Ishikawa Railway|Q11585936|qid=Q11585936|1=IR Ishikawa Railway}}

